sources.data_found: The Department of Computer Science at Central Michigan University offers a challenging and comprehensive program designed to prepare students for high-impact careers in technology. Programs emphasize both theoretical foundations and advanced practical skills with hands-on learning in specialized labs equipped with the latest software and tools.
Central Michigan University had a total enrollment of 14,399 students in 2023. The full-time enrollment is 11,065 students and the part-time enrollment is 3,334.

Included in this year's new student enrollment are 2,044 new First Time In Any College (freshman or first-year) students, 921 new transfer students and 1,238 graduate students. International students: 1,734 students representing 70 countries.
Central Michigan University has a total enrollment of 14,399 including 10,055 undergraduate students and 4,344 graduate students for academic year 2023-2024.
Central Michigan University's enrollment increased for the first time in over a decade, with 14,466 students enrolled this fall semester (2024).

student_data.notes: Central Michigan University Computer Science enrollment estimated based on university-wide data. Estimate based on typical CS program sizes at similar R2 universities (2-3% of total enrollment for CS undergrad, ~1% for CS grad). No PhD program found in Computer Science.
